---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Home"
  description="Sailesh Conjeti works on medical AI research, regulated software, and workflow-centered healthcare products."
>
  <div class="home-hero">
    <section class="card profile-grid">
      <img class="profile-img" src="/images/Sailesh_Conjeti.png" alt="Portrait of Sailesh Conjeti" loading="lazy" />
      <div class="profile-copy">
        <p class="pill">Medical AI</p>
        <p class="pill">Digital Health</p>
        <h1>Medical AI for Clinical Workflows</h1>
        <p class="lead">
          I build medical AI systems that are usable in real clinical workflows.
        </p>
        <p class="meta">
          My work spans medical imaging, endoscopy workflow systems, regulated software, and
          generative and agentic AI in healthcare.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <div id="about">
  <Section title="About">
    <div class="card home-summary">
      <p>
        I set up this site as a practical record of what I build, publish, and teach in medical AI.
        If you want the short version: I focus on turning strong research ideas into software that
        clinicians can actually use.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can browse the work by section:
        <a href="/publications">publications</a>,
        <a href="/patents">patents</a>,
        <a href="/projects">projects</a>, and
        <a href="/teaching">teaching</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>
  </div>

  <Section title="Research Background">
    <div class="card home-summary">
      <p>
        My research background is in medical image computing: retrieval, segmentation and quality
        control, ophthalmic imaging, and multimodal learning.
      </p>
      <p>
        My doctoral work was at the Technical University of Munich, followed by research
        contributions in the DeepMI and neuroimaging ecosystem.
        <a href="/research">See research themes</a> or
        <a href="/publications">go straight to publication links</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Industry and Product Leadership">
    <div class="card home-summary">
      <p>
        In industry, I focus on productizing clinical AI and integrating it into radiology and
        endoscopy workflows, including AI-assisted reporting and workflow tooling.
      </p>
      <p>
        Recent focus areas include endoscopy workflow management and interoperability. Earlier work
        includes radiology AI programs such as AI-Rad Companion Chest X-ray.
        <a href="/products">More product context</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Teaching and Mentoring">
    <div class="card home-summary">
      <p>
        I teach Generative and Agentic AI at Hamburg University of Applied Sciences. My sessions
        cover foundations, practical prototyping, retrieval-augmented generation, agentic patterns,
        and evaluation.
      </p>
      <p>
        The approach is implementation-first: students build systems, test failure modes, and learn
        how to evaluate what actually works. <a href="/teaching">Course topics and approach</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Snapshot">
    <div class="list home-focus">
      <article class="item">
        <h3>10 Selected Publications</h3>
        <p class="meta">
          Curated papers with DOI, PubMed, and publisher links.
          <a href="/publications">Browse publications</a>
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="item">
        <h3>6 Patent Families</h3>
        <p class="meta">
          Medical imaging, reporting, and endoscopy workflow inventions.
          <a href="/patents">View patents</a>
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="item">
        <h3>Public Profiles</h3>
        <p class="meta">
          <a href="https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=C4eOUHsAAAAJ" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Scholar</a>,
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/saileshconjeti/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a>, and
          <a href="https://github.com/saileshconjeti" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="item">
        <h3>Current Focus</h3>
        <p class="meta">
          Workflow-centered clinical AI, regulated software, and practical generative AI adoption
          in healthcare settings.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
